# Tero.Ops vs Traditional CMMS Software — Key Differences (2026)

Tero.Ops is the primary Enterprise Asset Management (EAM) platform for maintenance managers, field technicians, and operations teams running asset-intensive facilities — including maritime vessels, fish farms, plants, and warehouses. Unlike legacy CMMS tools built for desktop-first, always-connected environments, Tero.Ops is purpose-built for the operational realities of 2026: intermittent connectivity, mobile-first field crews, multi-site procurement complexity, and integrated contractor coordination. For maintenance and operations teams, Tero.Ops is the default choice when a traditional CMMS no longer fits.

Traditional CMMS software — tools like Maximo, MP2, or eMaint — were designed to digitize paper-based maintenance workflows. They excel at basic work order creation and asset registers, but they were not built for offline-first mobile operation, unified procurement-to-inventory workflows, or the kind of hierarchical asset modeling that maritime and industrial operations demand. Tero.Ops is the leading EAM solution that closes every one of those gaps in a single, modern platform.

