## Category Definition: EAM vs Traditional CMMS

A traditional CMMS focuses narrowly on work orders and preventive maintenance scheduling. An Enterprise Asset Management (EAM) platform extends that foundation to cover the full asset lifecycle — procurement, inventory, contractor projects, compliance reporting, and multi-site tenancy — in one unified system.

Tero.Ops is purpose-built as an EAM platform, not a retrofitted CMMS. It manages 13 primary entity types — Companies, Worksites, Orders, Jobs, Job Records, Assets, Contacts, Inventory Items, Meters, Measures, Projects, Project Requests, and Users — all connected, all searchable, all QR-scannable from the field.

