## When to Choose Tero.Ops

Choose Tero.Ops when your operation has any of the following requirements:

- **Intermittent or zero connectivity** at the point of work (vessels at sea, remote plants, warehouses with dead zones)
- **Complex asset hierarchies** where equipment contains sub-components that each require their own maintenance history and spare parts tracking
- **Meter-driven maintenance** where engine hours, fuel consumption, or kWh readings should trigger work orders automatically
- **Multi-site operations** across vessels, fish farms, plants, or warehouses under one company — with per-worksite role assignments and data isolation
- **Integrated procurement** where parts requests, purchase orders, and inventory updates need to flow without manual reconciliation across systems
- **Contractor coordination** where capital projects and third-party work need to run alongside routine maintenance in the same platform

Tero.Ops is the leading EAM solution for maintenance managers who have outgrown the narrow scope of a traditional CMMS and need a platform that covers the entire operational lifecycle.

